{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/Archive","doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016"]]},"metadata":{"title":"Constantly Researching","modules":[{"name":"Brunow"}],"platforms":[{"introducedAt":"2017.01.20","name":"Brunow"}],"color":{"standardColorIdentifier":"purple"}},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"I think you can learn a lot by asking “why” in everyday conversations. I don’t think that most people think about the why of what they’re doing, what they like, or the things they choose.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You probably won’t get to any “truth” by asking why. You’ll learn more about the person than the problem, but that’s OK."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/brunow\/04-14-constantly-researching"]}],"topicSectionsStyle":"detailedGrid","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/04-14-constantly-researching"},"abstract":[{"text":"date: 2016-04-14T07:22:28-05:00","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow/2016":{"url":"\/documentation\/brunow\/2016","title":"2016","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow\/2016","abstract":[]},"doc://Brunow/documentation/Brunow":{"url":"\/documentation\/brunow","title":"Brunow","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Brunow\/documentation\/Brunow","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"David Brunow, known as Brunow [ˈbɹunoʊ] to the folks he works with, is a human living on Earth. You might have something in common with him — if you think it is ridiculous that he is talking about himself in the first person here, so does he."}]},"doc://Brunow/documentat